rfare to Taipei  Taiwan  Eligibility Any current VMI cadet in good standing is eligible to apply  Applications must be received no later than 28 February 2015  Program  Cadets may choose three 1 credit courses from among the six offered  These course will be taught in English and no prior knowledge of the Chinese language is required  Topics in Explosive Chemical Warfare Information Security Technology An Introduction to Marine Vehicle Design Design Methodology of Aerial Vehicles Geospatial Data Processing Advance Light Source in Taiwan  Infrared Optical Principles and Processing Room and Board Students will be living with CCIT cadets in their barracks  Cadets will wear the class uniform  They will be able to participate in physical training and other aspects of daily life at CCIT  Cadets are exposed to many aspects of Taiwanes culture  Excursions in the past have included trips to Taipei  Longshaun Temple  Taipei 101  the Shi lin Night Market  and Sun Moon Lake  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 